            <bug_when>2009-09-09 21:16:03 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>The Scroller:_onClickHeader clears the selection. It does so because it assumes that the table model is unable to preserve the selection when the sort changes. Using my contributed &quot;smart&quot; table model, this assumption is no longer necessarily true; in some cases that model *does* preserve the selection across sort changes. Therefore, I would like to request that this behavior be controlled by a property. Better still, Scroller could simply fire a model event, and the model could decide what to do.

Workaround: subclass qx.ui.table.pane.Scroller and wholesale-replace the _onClickHeader method.</thetext>
